  <steps>
    <step order="0">Pre-wrap-up check: task 073 (post-deploy validation) ✅ in TASK-INDEX.md; all G1–G9 criteria PASS.</step>
    <step order="1">**Step 3.7 #1**: Run `/code-review` on all Action Engine project code. Targets: `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/`, `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/Action*.cs`, `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Jobs/ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler.cs`, `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/`, `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/GateApprovalCard/`. Capture report.</step>
    <step order="2">**Step 3.7 #1 cont.**: Fix critical (P0/P1) issues from code-review. Re-run code-review to confirm. Defer non-critical (P3) to R2 — log in lessons-learned.</step>
    <step order="3">**Step 3.7 #1 cont.**: Run `/adr-check` on all Action Engine code. Verify all 15 applicable ADRs (per project CLAUDE.md §Resources). Capture report. Fix violations.</step>
    <step order="3.5">Verify G11 (every Action Engine endpoint has endpoint-filter auth) via grep audit: `Grep` for `MapPost|MapGet|MapPut` in Action Engine endpoints + verify `.AddEndpointFilter` on each.</step>
    <step order="3.6">Verify G12 (no CRUD-side caller injects AE internals) via grep audit: `Grep` for `IActionOrchestrationService` references outside `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/` — should find ZERO. If non-zero, refactor consumer to use `IActionEngineFacade`.</step>
    <step order="4">**Step 3.7 #2**: Run `/repo-cleanup projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`. Review cleanup report; approve removals of `notes/debug/`, `notes/spikes/` (intermediate spike files; final reports keep), `notes/drafts/`; archive `notes/handoffs/` → `.archive/`.</step>
    <step order="5">Checkpoint via `context-handoff` (mandatory after Step 3 + 4 — 3+ completed wrap-up steps).</step>
    <step order="6">**Step 3.7 #3**: Update `README.md`:
      - Status → **Complete**
      - Last Updated → today
      - Phase → Complete; Progress → 100%
      - Completed Date → today
      - Check ALL 12 graduation criteria (G1–G12) checkboxes ✅
      - Add Changelog entry: "Project complete; merged to master {date}; lessons-learned at notes/lessons-learned.md"</step>
    <step order="7">**Step 3.7 #4**: Update `plan.md`:
      - Status → **Complete**
      - All milestone statuses → ✅
      - Add a footer "Outcomes" section linking lessons-learned + verifying task references for each criterion</step>
    <step order="8">**Step 3.7 #5**: Create `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/lessons-learned.md`. Include: what worked (e.g., Hybrid D reuse, parallel-group execution), what didn't (e.g., specific bloat surprises, scheduler-choice churn), what to carry to R2 (e.g., Visual Builder, Conversational Builder Agent, signal-triggered Monitors, expanded template library).</step>
    <step order="9">**Step 3.7 #6**: Final verification:
      - `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: ALL tasks ✅ (including 090)
      - `current-task.md`: set to "none — project complete; ready for merge-to-master"
      - All docs current; no critical issues remaining; cleanup completed
      - All 12 graduation criteria ✅ in README</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run `/adr-check` and `/code-review` as quality gates per FULL rigor — confirm no regressions from wrap-up edits to README/plan.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 090 status ✅ (final task). Update `current-task.md` to "none — project complete".</step>
    <step order="11">Document deviations under `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/`. Recommend next action to user: "Project complete; run `/merge-to-master` to merge `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1` into `master`."</step>
  </steps>

